   <div id=\"full-gallery-numbers\"><span class=\"mlp_current_page\"></span> of <span class=\"mlp_total_page\"></span></div>\n                    <a id=\"mlp_next_arrow\" class=\"right arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_next_arrow\" href=\"#\">></a>\n                </div>\n\n\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-tablets\"></div>\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-mobiles\"></div>\n\n\n               <div id=\"mlp_info\" class=\"twelve columns\">\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-title\"><span class=\"mlp_current_title\"></span></div>\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-desc\">\n                        <span class=\"mlp_current_desc\"></span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n<p><em>Photo gallery curated by Christie Vuong.</em></p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>Related: </strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/why-giving-a-grammy-to-beck-was-the-perfectly-wrong-choice/\" target=\"_blank\">Why Beck’s Grammy win for Best Album was a perfect, terrible choice</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/uncategorized/sia-at-the-grammys/\" target=\"_blank\">Looking at the genius—and fatal misstep—of Sia</a><br />\n<a title=\"The Interview: Grammy winner Sam Smith\" href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/culture/arts/the-interview-sam-smith-on-why-hes-a-feminist/\" target=\"_blank\">Our Q&A with breakout star Sam Smith</a></p></blockquote>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-gallery-relive-the-2015-grammys/\">Photo gallery: Relive the 2015 Grammys</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-gallery-relive-the-2015-grammys/feed/","slash:comments":"0"},{"title":"Maclean’s on the Hill: Assisted suicide, Bill C-51, John Baird","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-feb-6-2015/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-feb-6-2015/#comments","pubDate":"Sat, 07 Feb 2015 03:41:40 +0000","dc:creator":"macleans.ca","category":["Ottawa","Podcast","Politics","Maclean's on the Hill"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=675725","description":"<p>The Maclean's Ottawa bureau revisits the week that was </p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-feb-6-2015/\">Maclean’s on the Hill: Assisted suicide, Bill C-51, John Baird</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean’s</em> politics team and Rogers radio’s Cormac MacSweeney sit down to hash out the week’s news in Ottawa.</p>\n<p>This week, we look closer at the Supreme Court’s ruling on assisted suicide, the government’s new anti-terror legislation and John Baird’s resignation.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ca/podcast/macleans.ca-podcast/id884074529?mt=2\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Subscribe on iTunes today,</strong></a> or play below, on <a href=\"http://www.stitcher.com/podcast/macleans-on-the-hill\" target=\"_blank\">Stitcher</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"width:720px;height:360px;border:0;overflow:hidden;\" width=\"720\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://app.stitcher.com/splayer/f/58030?el=1&refid=stpr\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/exit-john-baird-stage-right/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/BAIRD-tile-1-300x299.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON RESIGNATIONS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Exit John Baird, stage right</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/a-man-for-all-questions/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/BAIRD-tile-2-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON BAIRD</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The minister’s many faces</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/economy/economicanalysis/the-a-to-z-of-the-oil-crash-an-encyclopedic-look-at-the-crisis/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/OIL_Banner2-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON OIL</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The A to Z of plummeting prices</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/the-heart-of-our-democracy-in-time-terror/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/QP-Live-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON RED TAPE</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Wherry defends Parliament</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/on-assisted-suicide-the-supreme-court-confronts-parliaments-cowardice/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/MAC07_ASSISTED_SUCIDE_THUMBNAIL.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON DYING</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The Supreme Court’s latest landmark</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/a-possible-compromise-on-the-census/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/STATS_CAN_THUMBNAIL01.jpeg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON A CENSUS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A medium-form compromise?</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/episode50.mp3\"><br />\nDownload this podcast. </a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-feb-6-2015/\">Maclean’s on the Hill: Assisted suicide, Bill C-51, John Baird</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-feb-6-2015/feed/","slash:comments":"0"},{"title":"Week in pictures","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/week-in-pictures-89/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/week-in-pictures-89/#comments","pubDate":"Fri, 06 Feb 2015 23:50:58 +0000","dc:creator":"Andrew Tolson","category":["Andrew Tolson","Photo"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=676075","description":"<p>A curated selection of the best shots from the week that was</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/week-in-pictures-89/\">Week in pictures</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><script type='text/javascript'>var image_max_height = \"500\";</script><script type='text/javascript'>var imagesArray = [{\"id\":676025,\"mlpId\":\"6473\",\"src\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/07899528-660x294.jpg\",\"width\":660,\"height\":294,\"medSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/07899528-150x150.jpg\",\"medWidth\":150,\"medHeight\":150,\"smallSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/02\\/07899528-150x150.jpg\",\"smallWidth\":150,\"smallHeight\":150,\"tagSlugs\":\"\",\"tagNames\":\"\",\"title\":\"Taipei, Taiwan\",\"caption\":\"\",\"loaded\":false,\"description\":\"At least 35 people died after a TransAsia Airways plane clipped a bridge and crashed into a river near the Taiwanese capital, Taipei. Fifty-eight people were on-board the domestic flight. The plane is now half-su