/politics/ottawa/politics-panel-jan-23/\">Politics Panel: How Ottawa prepares for a spring sitting</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>Each week, the Maclean’s Ottawa bureau sits down to discuss the stories behind the week’s stories in our politics podcast, On The Hill. They also gather in the OMNI studios to talk about the stories that matter. This week, the panel previews the spring sitting of Parliament.</p>\n<div itemprop=\"video\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\"><div style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<object id=\"2036826638\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\n<param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateReady\" />\n<param name=\"templateLoadHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateLoaded\" />\n<param name=\"includeAPI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"width\" value=\"822\" />\n<param name=\"height\" value=\"462\" /><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"781201057001\" /><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"4007890448001\" /></object><meta itemprop='name' content='Maclean's Politics Panel, Jan. 23' /><meta itemprop='thumbnail' content='http://newsandbusiness.rogersdigitalmedia.com.edgesuite.net/bcassets/13639244001/201501/220/13639244001_4007950808001_OTTAWA-MACLEANS-1300-2015JAN23-2-th.jpg?pubId=13639244001' /><meta itemprop='duration' content='PT17M59S' /><meta itemprop='description' content='Maclean's Politics Panel, Jan. 23' /></div>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/politics-panel-jan-23/\">Politics Panel: How Ottawa prepares for a spring sitting</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/politics-panel-jan-23/feed/","slash:comments":"0"},{"title":"Maclean’s on the Hill: A preview of Parliament’s spring session","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-preview-of-parliaments-spring-session/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-preview-of-parliaments-spring-session/#comments","pubDate":"Fri, 23 Jan 2015 23:27:32 +0000","dc:creator":"macleans.ca","category":["Ottawa","Podcast","Politics","Maclean's on the Hill"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=669595","description":"<p>Our Ottawa bureau on what's in store for the nation's capital</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-preview-of-parliaments-spring-session/\">Maclean’s on the Hill: A preview of Parliament’s spring session</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean’s</em> politics team and Rogers radio’s Cormac Mac Sweeney sit down to hash out the week’s news in Ottawa. This week, we talk to Finance Minister Joe Oliver about the drop in oil prices and how an economic downturn could influence his budget, we speak with the author of the <em>Maclean’s</em> cover story that calls out racism in Winnipeg, and the <em>Maclean’s</em> panel previews the upcoming spring sitting of Parliament. <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ca/podcast/macleans.ca-podcast/id884074529?mt=2\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Subscribe on iTunes today,</strong></a> or play below, on <a href=\"http://www.stitcher.com/podcast/macleans-on-the-hill\" target=\"_blank\">Stitcher</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"width:720px;height:360px;border:0;overflow:hidden;\" width=\"720\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://app.stitcher.com/splayer/f/58030?el=1&refid=stpr\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-politics-of-polozs-economic-outlook/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MAC46_COSH_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON POLOZ</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The politics of a rate cut</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/world/bringing-canadas-role-in-iraq-into-focus/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/CF-18-featured.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON IRAQ</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Canadians are at war</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/the-wildrose-identity-crisis/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC04_COSH_FEATURE.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON WILDROSE</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">What’s left of Alberta’s opposition</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/welcome-to-winnipeg-where-canadas-racism-problem-is-at-its-worst/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC04_WINNIPEG_GILMORE_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON WINNIPEG</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Racism ravages the prairie city</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/worldpolitics/what-really-happens-in-davos/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/gilmore.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON DAVOS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">The global elite love to party</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/washington/obamas-brand-of-hope-now-a-plea-for-unity/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Obama-2008-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON OBAMA</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">A president desperate for unity</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/episode48.mp3\">Download this podcast.</a></p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-preview-of-parliaments-spring-session/\">Maclean’s on the Hill: A preview of Parliament’s spring session</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/macleans-on-the-hill-a-preview-of-parliaments-spring-session/feed/","slash:comments":"0"},{"title":"Photo essay: Otherworldly selfies in the natural world","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-essay-otherworldly-selfies-in-the-natural-world/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-essay-otherworldly-selfies-in-the-natural-world/#comments","pubDate":"Sun, 18 Jan 2015 19:16:54 +0000","dc:creator":"Aaron Hutchins","category":["Photo","Banff National Park","Paul Zizka","photo essay","selfies"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=664967","description":"<p>Paul Zizka put himself in his photos and the magic that he feels in mountains emerged</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-essay-otherworldly-selfies-in-the-natural-world/\">Photo essay: Otherworldly selfies in the natural world</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><script type='text/javascript'>var image_max_height = \"500\";</script><script type='text/javascript'>var imagesArray = [{\"id\":665075,\"mlpId\":\"6289\",\"src\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC03_PHOTOESSAY_PAULZIZKA_POST12-660x440.jpg\",\"width\":660,\"height\":440,\"medSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC03_PHOTOESSAY_PAULZIZKA_POST12-150x150.jpg\",\"medWidth\":150,\"medHeight\":150,\"smallSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC03_PHOTOESSAY_PAULZIZKA_POST12-150x150.jpg\",\"smallWidth\":150,\"smallHeight\":150,\"tagSlugs\":\"\",\"tagNames\":\"\",\"title\":\"Paul Zizka Photo Essay\",\"caption\":\"\",\"loaded\":false,\"description\":\"'Emerald Fortress', Aurora borealis over Castle Mountain, Banff National Park, Alberta, Canada.\",\"order\":\"1\",\"imageCount\":\"9\",\"alt\":\"\"}];</script><a name='gallery_top' id='gallery_top'></a><a name='mobile_gallery_top' id='mobile_gallery_top'></a>\n<div id='mlp_ajax_loader'><img src='http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/plugins/media-library-plus/images/ajax-loader.gif' /></div>\n<div id=\"universal_mlp_container\">\n\n<div id=\"mlp_gallery_viewer\">\n\n\t<div id=\"mlp_nav_image_container\">\n\n\t\t<div id=\"image_container\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_next_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_prev_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n        <div class=\"mlp_next_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_next_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_arrow_container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mlp_inner_nav\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"></a>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_next_zone mlp_arrow_container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mlp_inner_nav\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\"></a>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t</div>\n    <div id=\"mlp_caption\"><span class=\"mlp_current_caption\"></span></div>\n\n    <div class=\"mlp_mobile_nav show-on-phones\">\n        <div id=\"full-gallery-nav\">\n            <a id=\"mlp_prev_arrow\" class=\"left arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_prev_arrow\" href=\"#\"><</a>\n            <a id=\"mlp_next_arrow\" class=\"right arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_next_arrow\" href=\"#\">></a>\n        </div>\n        <div id=\"full-gallery-numbers\"><span class=\"hide-on-phones\">Photo </span><b><span class=\"mlp_current_page\"></span></b> of <b><span class=\"mlp_total_page\"></span></b></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n            <div class=\"row\">\n\n                <div id=\"full-gallery-nav\">\n                    <a id=\"mlp_prev_arrow\" class=\"left arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_prev_arrow\" href=\"#\"><</a>\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-numbers\"><span class=\"mlp_current_page\"></span> of <span class=\"mlp_total_page\"></span></div>\n                    <a id=\"mlp_next_arrow\" class=\"right arrow mlp_arrow_button mlp_next_arrow\" href=\"#\">></a>\n                </div>\n\n\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-tablets\"></div>\n                <div class=\"clear show-on-mobiles\"></div>\n\n\n               <div id=\"mlp_info\" class=\"twelve columns\">\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-title\"><span class=\"mlp_current_title\"></span></div>\n                    <div id=\"full-gallery-desc\">\n                        <span class=\"mlp_current_desc\"></span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n<p>For years, <a href=\"http://zizka.ca/\">Paul Zizka</a> used to dislike photos of the wilderness if there was a human element to them. No people. No buildings. But then, on a picturesque winter’s night walking alone along the shore of Lake Minnewanka, Alta., Zizka just couldn’t find the perfect foreground. So, he put himself in the picture. What he discovered was that the photo told an entirely different story. “Sometimes, if you include a person, you can convey a sense of vulnerability,” he says from his home in Banff, Alta. “It makes some people think: ‘That’s the last place I’d want to be.’ Or sometimes it’s: ‘That’s the first place I’d want to be.’ A moment of bliss in the mountains.”</p>\n<p>Before taking any self-portraits, Zizka will shoot the entire scene without any man or man-made elements. Then, once he’s done with his nature shots, he’ll jump on the other side of the lens and get creative. Rarely will you see Zizka’s face in his self-portraits, however. “It would make the image more about me,” he says, “than the magic of having a person there, part of nature.”</p>\n<p>It can be lonely work. The wind is howling. The mountains can be intimidating. And how many people are willing to venture out alone into the cold winter’s night and wait for hours for that perfect background to shoot? “You hear the odd noise in the bush and you know there’s nobody around for kilometres,” he says. “It can be a bit daunting.” He has pictures to prove it.</p>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-essay-otherworldly-selfies-in-the-natural-world/\">Photo essay: Otherworldly selfies in the natural world</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/multimedia/photo/photo-essay-otherworldly-selfies-in-the-natural-world/feed/","slash:comments":"0"},{"title":"Politics Panel: How Canada responds to terror threats","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-politics-panel-how-canada-responds-to-terror-threats/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-politics-panel-how-canada-responds-to-terror-threats/#comments","pubDate":"Sat, 17 Jan 2015 14:31:05 +0000","dc:creator":"macleans.ca","category":["Ottawa","Politics","Video","The Maclean's Politics Panel"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=666905","description":"<p>The Ottawa bureau hashes out the issues that matter</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-politics-panel-how-canada-responds-to-terror-threats/\">Politics Panel: How Canada responds to terror threats</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p>Each week, the Maclean’s Ottawa bureau sits down to discuss the stories behind the week’s stories in <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-budgets-election-prep-terrorism/\">our politics podcast, On The Hill.</a></p>\n<p>They also gather in the OMNI studios to talk about the stories that matter. This week, in the wake of the Paris shootings, they muse about Canada’s response to increased concern about terrorist threats.</p>\n<div itemprop=\"video\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\"><div style=\"display:none\"></div>\n<object id=\"1141814489\" class=\"BrightcoveExperience\"><param name=\"bgcolor\" value=\"#FFFFFF\" />\n<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\n<param name=\"templateReadyHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateReady\" />\n<param name=\"templateLoadHandler\" value=\"rdm_foundation_bc_onTemplateLoaded\" />\n<param name=\"includeAPI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isVid\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"isUI\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"dynamicStreaming\" value=\"true\" />\n<param name=\"width\" value=\"822\" />\n<param name=\"height\" value=\"360\" /><param name=\"playerID\" value=\"781201057001\" /><param name=\"@videoPlayer\" value=\"3994510225001\" /></object><meta itemprop='name' content='Maclean's politics panel, Jan. 16' /><meta itemprop='thumbnail' content='http://newsandbusiness.rogersdigitalmedia.com.edgesuite.net/bcassets/13639244001/201501/2599/13639244001_3994542891001_OTTAWA-MACLEANS-1600-2015JAN16-1-th.jpg?pubId=13639244001' /><meta itemprop='duration' content='PT9M2S' /><meta itemprop='description' content='Maclean's politics panel, Jan. 16' /></div>\n</span><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-politics-panel-how-canada-responds-to-terror-threats/\">Politics Panel: How Canada responds to terror threats</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","wfw:commentRss":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/the-macleans-politics-panel-how-canada-responds-to-terror-threats/feed/","slash:comments":"1"},{"title":"Maclean’s on the Hill: Budgets, election prep, terrorism","link":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-budgets-election-prep-terrorism/","comments":"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-budgets-election-prep-terrorism/#comments","pubDate":"Sat, 17 Jan 2015 00:13:36 +0000","dc:creator":"macleans.ca","category":["Ottawa","Podcast","Politics","Maclean's on the Hill"],"guid":"http://www.macleans.ca/?p=666817","description":"<p>Also: Bill Blair's possible political career</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/macleans-on-the-hill-budgets-election-prep-terrorism/\">Maclean’s on the Hill: Budgets, election prep, terrorism</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><p><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-514329\" alt=\"podcast\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ON-THE-HILL.jpg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" /></a></p>\n<p>Each week, the <em>Maclean’s</em> politics team and Rogers radio’s Cormac MacSweeney sit down to hash out the week’s news in Ottawa. This week, we talk to former parliamentary budget officer Kevin Page and TD Bank chief economist Craig Alexander about the state of the federal budget and the economy, Elections Canada explains how it’s getting ready for an election and we consider Toronto police chief Bill Blair’s possible entry into politics and the Harper government’s coming legislation to deal with the threat of terrorism. <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/ca/podcast/macleans.ca-podcast/id884074529?mt=2\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Subscribe on iTunes today,</a> or play below, on <a href=\"http://www.stitcher.com/podcast/macleans-on-the-hill\" target=\"_blank\">Stitcher</a>. </strong></p>\n<p><iframe scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"width:720px;height:180px;border:0;overflow:hidden;\" width=\"720\" height=\"180\" src=\"http://app.stitcher.com/splayer/f/58030/36668062?el=0&refid=stpr\"></iframe></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">THE HEADLINES</h1>\n<ul class=\"block-grid mobile two-up\">\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/worldpolitics/why-muslim-world-decline/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/MAC03_PARIS_VIDEO_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON ISLAM</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Why the Muslim world is left behind</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/history-discretion-and-how-to-settle-an-election/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/House-empty-822x462-300x300.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON ELECTIONS</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Campaigns that stick out</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/how-many-ministers-do-we-really-need/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Shuffle1445x290-300x300-1421356960.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON CABINET</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">How many ministers do we need?</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.macleans.ca/politics/thinking-out-loud-about-an-alberta-pst/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/MAC43_COSH_FEATURE01.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /> <strong>ON TAX</strong></a><br />\n<em style=\"line-height: 19px;\">Jim Prentice mulls a PST</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p s