=\"http://www.macleans.ca\">Macleans.ca</a>.</p>","content:encoded":"<span itemprop=\"articleBody\" class=\"entry-content\"><script type='text/javascript'>var image_max_height = \"500\";</script><script type='text/javascript'>var imagesArray = [{\"id\":660883,\"mlpId\":\"6117\",\"src\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC02_PARIS_SHOOTING01-660x440.jpg\",\"width\":660,\"height\":440,\"medSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC02_PARIS_SHOOTING01-150x150.jpg\",\"medWidth\":150,\"medHeight\":150,\"smallSrc\":\"http:\\/\\/www.macleans.ca\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/01\\/MAC02_PARIS_SHOOTING01-150x150.jpg\",\"smallWidth\":150,\"smallHeight\":150,\"tagSlugs\":\"\",\"tagNames\":\"\",\"title\":\"Paris shooting\",\"caption\":\"\",\"loaded\":false,\"description\":\"French Prime Minister Manuel Valls, centre, looks up at the building housing the satirical newspaper\\u00a0<em>Charlie Hebdo<\\/em>. Masked gunmen stormed the paper's offices late Wednesday morning, Paris time, killing at least 12 people before escaping. The weekly has previously drawn condemnation from Muslims. (Francois Mori\\/AP)\",\"order\":\"1\",\"imageCount\":\"11\",\"alt\":\"\"}];</script><a name='gallery_top' id='gallery_top'></a><a name='mobile_gallery_top' id='mobile_gallery_top'></a>\n<div id='mlp_ajax_loader'><img src='http://www.macleans.ca/wp-content/plugins/media-library-plus/images/ajax-loader.gif' /></div>\n<div id=\"universal_mlp_container\">\n\n<div id=\"mlp_gallery_viewer\">\n\n\t<div id=\"mlp_nav_image_container\">\n\n\t\t<div id=\"image_container\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_next_zone mlp_shadow_zone\"></div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_prev_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n        <div class=\"mlp_next_detector mlp_detector\" id=\"mlp_next_detector\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"mlp_prev_zone mlp_arrow_container\">\n\t\t\t<div class